Sentencas: A novel procedure to make self-supporting thin yttria-stabilised zirconia (YSZ) membranes by laser machining is shown.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: We have used a galvanometric controlled laser beam to machine the surface of a conventional sintered YSZ plate and achieved thin areas up to 10 mu m thick, but also maintaining thicker support beams to ensure the structural strength of the membrane.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: The outer areas of the plate are left unaltered to facilitate the sealing of the cell.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: This kind of thin membrane is ideal for preparing electrolyte-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFC) operating at intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: The membranes have been characterized by optical profilometry, Raman Spectroscopy and Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: The YSZ properties, except those derived from membrane thinning, remain unaltered by processing.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: Using the laser machined YSZ electrolyte a conventional electrolyte supported YSZ-Ni/YSZ/LSM-YSZ planar single cell with average electrolyte thickness of less than 50 mu m has been fabricated and characterized.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining

Sentencas: Performance of the cell is improved as a result of the thinning process.
Titulo: Self-Supporting Thin Yttria-Stabilised Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Prepared by Laser Machining
